Firecracker microVM deployment (Tier 2 runtime isolation)
==========================================================

Overview
--------
Tier 2 isolates each destructive tool call inside a fresh Firecracker microVM.
The Python wrapper in tessera.runtime.firecracker provides the API; this
directory supplies the operator-facing artifacts.

Prerequisites
-------------
- Linux host (x86_64 or aarch64). Firecracker does not run on macOS.
- firecracker >= 1.5 binary on PATH (https://github.com/firecracker-microvm/firecracker/releases)
- jailer (bundled with the firecracker release) for production isolation.
- A vmlinux-format kernel image (5.10 LTS recommended).
- An ext4 root filesystem image containing the tessera-guest-agent binary.

Files in this directory
-----------------------
  vm-config.json          Reference VM configuration for a single microVM
                          instance. Pass to firecracker --config-file.
  firecracker@.service    systemd unit for per-instance VM management.
                          Parametrize with the vm_id: firecracker@<vm_id>.service

Environment variables consumed by tessera.runtime.firecracker
--------------------------------------------------------------
  TESSERA_RUNTIME_TIER    Set to "2" to enable microVM isolation. Default: "1".
  TESSERA_FC_KERNEL       Absolute path to the vmlinux kernel image.
  TESSERA_FC_ROOTFS       Absolute path to the ext4 root filesystem image.

VM snapshot workflow (production)
-----------------------------------
Pre-warm a base VM snapshot and restore it per call to keep gate overhead
below 5 ms. The rough flow:

  1. Start a base VM from vm-config.json:
       firecracker --no-api --config-file vm-config.json --id base

  2. When the guest is ready, create a snapshot:
       curl -X PUT http://${FIRECRACKER_SOCK}/snapshot/create \
         -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
         -d '{"snapshot_type":"Full","snapshot_path":"/var/tessera/base.snap","mem_file_path":"/var/tessera/base.mem"}'

  3. For each tool call, restore from snapshot:
       curl -X PUT http://${FIRECRACKER_SOCK}/snapshot/load \
         -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
         -d '{"snapshot_path":"/var/tessera/base.snap","mem_backend":{"backend_type":"File","backend_path":"/var/tessera/base.mem"}}'

Security notes
--------------
- Run firecracker under jailer to confine it to its own mount + network + PID
  namespace. See the jailer documentation at:
  https://github.com/firecracker-microvm/firecracker/blob/main/docs/jailer.md
- The root filesystem image should be built with a minimal read-only base.
  The guest agent binary and its dependencies are the only executables needed.
- Do not share kernel images or rootfs images across security domains.
